* PROJECTS

Costing and Profit spreadsheet (Wilfredo’s Ice Cream Co.):
This spreadsheet was built to ascertain how much the business had to charge for its ice cream. It tied in with the Wilfredo’s Ice Cream company’s finances to show proﬁt from input costs of the ice cream, ongoing expenses, and cost price charged. Ultimately it gave the managers insight into the sustainability of the ice cream business model and saved tens of millions of rands by showing that ultimately the business wasn’t sustainable.

Home budget spreadsheet tool:
Bruce designed a home budget tool to keep track of expenses and show where deviations in a tight household budget were happening. This can be adapted to a business use. The next step is to code all the concepts and ultimately to tie it into an R or Julia package so that everyone can use it.

Investment analysis scripted document:
Bruce wrote an experimental org script in Emacs to pull stock prices oﬀ the internet, and to reﬂect the valuations on investments. He further incorporated exchange rates. Bruce stored crucial values to a Sqlite3 database and charted the continuously updated data with a time series chart from R. Latterly he has converted some of the code to R and is performing optimisations on portfolio’s with some of the specialist packages in R.

       
